genresAdvancedInfo.name: vintage dutch pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Vintage Dutch pop refers to the pop music that was popular in the Netherlands in the 1960s and 1970s. It is characterized by catchy melodies, upbeat rhythms, and lyrics that often deal with love and relationships. The music is often accompanied by electric guitars, drums, and keyboards, and it has a distinct sound that is both nostalgic and fun.
